# Way of Pi web UI ↔ Pi backend (critical)

## CRITICAL — product lock (agents + tools)

- **Every workspace agent** (orchestrator + every **`.pi/agents/*.md`** persona) **must** ultimately run against the **same Pi coding-agent engine** as the TUI: **`extensions[]`**, **`registerTool`**, **slash commands**, **`dispatch_agent`**, **skills**, **hooks**, **session JSONL**, and **provider/model routing** as loaded by **`WOP_PI_BINARY`** with workspace cwd and **`WOP_HOME`** isolation per **`docs/WOP_NAMESPACE.md`**.
- **Authoritative rule:** If Pi can do it, **Way of Pi must not ship a second “mini Pi”** in Bun (parallel tool registry, fake extension execution, or chat that implies Pi ran a tool when only Bun did). **Bun-only** paths (**`server/chat.ts`**, **`server/chat-orchestrator-tools.ts`**, **`server/orchestrator-tools-exec.ts`**, direct Ollama/OpenRouter) are **interim** only and **must** be replaced or tunneled through headless Pi with a **dated milestone** in **`docs/WOP_PI_BACKEND_WIRING_PLAN.md`** and **`docs/WOP_OPEN_TODOS.md`**.
- **Building missing functions** takes priority over expanding interim Bun behavior: implement **`docs/WOP_PI_BACKEND_WIRING_PLAN.md`** Phase **2** (single chat through Pi) → **4** (`dispatch_agent` / multi-agent) → runtime **manifest** — not more Bun-native “tool loops.”
- **`WOP_CHAT_ENGINE=pi`:** Chat **must not** silently use the interim Bun provider; turns run **`pi --mode json`** when **`pi`** resolves. If the CLI is missing, the server rejects the turn (**`piAgentRuntimeBlockedReason`**). **`WOP_CHAT_ENGINE=auto`** uses Pi when the CLI resolves and otherwise falls back to Bun — same **`pi --mode json`** path for **all** workspace personas when Pi is available (full built-ins + **`.pi/settings.json`** extensions).

## Do not build or own “the agent system” — use Pi’s

- **Way of Pi owns:** the **shell** (editor, tree, layout, menus), **workspace host I/O** where Pi does not (jailed **`/api/file`**, etc.), **`WOP_*`** isolation, and **glue** that **starts / attaches / proxies** **`WOP_PI_BINARY`** and translates HTTP/WebSocket to Pi.
- **Pi owns:** **agent** behavior end-to-end — **`extensions[]`**, **tools**, **slash commands**, **`dispatch_agent`**, **skills**, **hooks**, **sessions**, **provider/model** inside the coding-agent process. That is **not** reimplemented in Bun.
- **Forbidden:** a first-party “Way of Pi agent runtime”, “WOP dispatch”, or any **parallel** chat+tool+extension stack that duplicates Pi’s semantics feature-by-feature. **Integrate** Pi; do **not** replace it with a home-grown system.

## North star — **Pi as backend (maximize)**

- **Default engineering direction:** Treat **headless Pi** (same **`extensions[]`**, skills, tools, sessions, provider stack as the TUI) as the **authoritative runtime** behind **`apps/wayofpi-ui/server/`**. Prefer **spawning, attaching, or proxying Pi** for any capability Pi already owns instead of growing a **second parallel** “mini Pi” inside Bun (duplicate chat, tool registry, slash commands, session format, or model routing).
- **Interim bridges are temporary:** Direct **Ollama / OpenRouter** in the Bun server exists as a **transition path** only. **New features** should integrate **through Pi** (or a documented Pi sidecar) unless explicitly scoped as pre-Pi infrastructure — and that scope must be **called out** in **`docs/WOP_PI_BACKEND_WIRING_PLAN.md`** / **`docs/WOP_OPEN_TODOS.md`** with a **time-bounded** follow-up to fold into Pi.
- **Configuration alignment:** Reuse **Pi’s on-disk and env conventions** where practical (e.g. repo **`.env`**, **`agent/settings.json`**, **`OLLAMA_*`** / workspace **`agent/`**) so one workspace truth feeds both TUI and web until a single Pi process owns chat. **`server/pi-ollama-env.ts`** is the pattern: bridge env shapes, do not fork unrelated names without **`WOP_*`** / **`docs/WOP_NAMESPACE.md`** justification.
- **When in doubt:** Add the **real Pi path** (HTTP forward, WebSocket tunnel, subprocess contract) or **shrink the UI** to stub — do **not** deepen bespoke Bun-only behavior that Pi will have to replace later.

## Non-negotiable

- **`apps/wayofpi-ui/`** affordances that mirror **Pi** (agents, teams, tools, extensions, chat/session behavior, model selection, orchestration, terminals, workspace operations) must be **actually implemented** against the **Way of Pi server** (`apps/wayofpi-ui/server/`), **Pi CLI/runtime**, or another **documented bridge** — not controls that only change local React state while implying Pi did the work.
- If **full Pi parity** for a feature is **not** shipped yet, the UI must **not masquerade as complete**: use explicit **stub / not wired** labeling, disable the control, or hide it until the backend exists — and track the gap in **`docs/WOP_*.md`**, **`docs/PLAN_*.md`** (non-WOP plans), or **`docs/WOP_OPEN_TODOS.md`**.
- **`/api/*`** and **`/ws`** are part of the product surface. Do not merge client changes that depend on new server behavior **without** the server (or document a breaking follow-up blocked on the same milestone).

## Implementation discipline

- **Simple** and **technical** UI modes share the **same product**: prefer **one real data path** (shared hooks, shared handlers). Do not add a feature in one mode and leave the other as a non-functional duplicate without a tracked, time-bounded gap.
- **Agents and teams** — follow **`.cursor/rules/wop-ui-workspace-agents.mdc`** (catalog, WebSocket persona, **`teams.yaml`**, and the distinction between **merged system prompt** vs real **`dispatch_agent`** / subprocess orchestration).
- **Layout and docks** — follow **`.cursor/rules/wop-ui-modular-docks.mdc`** so new Pi-backed panels stay modular and persistent without forking the shell per mode.
- **Isolation and naming** — respect **`WOP_*`**, **`docs/WOP_NAMESPACE.md`**, and **`docs/WOP_STANDALONE_SYSTEM_PLAN.md`** so the UI never blurs **Way of Pi** with upstream **`pi`** identifiers or processes.

## Contract docs (keep in sync when behavior changes)

- **`docs/WOP_PI_BACKEND_WIRING_PLAN.md`** — master map: HTTP/WebSocket inventory, UI surface matrix, phased Pi integration (**§0** = critical lock).
- **`docs/WOP_TECHNICAL_UI.md`** — shell, hooks, server boundaries.
- **`docs/WOP_MULTI_AGENT_WEBSOCKET.md`** — multi-agent / orchestration events when implemented.
- **`docs/WOP_WORKSPACE_AGENTS_UI_PLAN.md`** — agent UI roadmap and Pi alignment phases.
- **`apps/wayofpi-ui/server/pi-agent-runtime.ts`** — Pi engine gate + reserved **`runPiChatTurn`** hook.

When you add or change Pi-facing UI, **verify** the backend path (API, WebSocket message, or Pi spawn) in code — do not ship “looks done” without it.
